**[1870, 02-24] Ms.A.1.2.36.109**

Mott to RDW. “The great questions of the time—Woman’s Rights &c.—seem to
be claiming simultaneous interest in Europe & America. Poor man has only
to meet coming results with the best grace he can. The lectures of
Horace Greely and others, stating how far they are disposed to
{u}let{/u} woman exercise her rights, are simply amusing because so
childish, so behind the demands of {u}now{/u}.”


